description: From Middle English milwell (amid many other forms), from Anglo-Norman meluel (amid other forms) and  Old French moluel, probably from moruel, from Old Breton mor (“sea”) (from Proto-Brythonic *mor) + Old French lus and luz (“pike, [as sea-luce] hake”) + -el (diminutive suffix).

entries.meaning: (Scotland, dialectal or historical) The Atlantic cod (Gadus morhua).
